Package: germlinevaR
Title: Convert, Filter and Summarise VEP-Annotated Germline Variant Calls
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Thiago", "Loreto Matos", 
           email = "thiago-loreto@hotmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Thiago Loreto Matos <thiago-loreto@hotmail.com>
Description: 
    Tools for working with VEP-annotated, single-sample germline variant calls
    (GATK HaplotypeCaller -> CNN tranches -> Ensembl VEP, hg38). Converts one or
    many per-sample VCFs into a maftools-style MAF data.table (one row per ALT
    allele, a single most-severe transcript per allele) without depending on
    maftools, optionally applying a depth/genotype-quality filter and a Brazilian
    ABraOM SABE-609 allele-frequency annotation. Provides population-frequency,
    clinical-significance and biotype filtering, a multi-section cohort summary
    with optional Excel and multi-page PDF report export, and a maftools-style
    oncoplot of the most-mutated genes.
